                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860A.01/7–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting Representative to the Provisional Government of the French Republic
                        at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-14T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 14, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2192. For Murphy. Your 2345, July 9, 9 p.m. Department agrees with Foreign Office
                    that AMG should not be established within the Republic of San Marino unless the
                    local Government has ceased to exist and if a neutral government cannot be made
                    to function.</p>
                <p>Sent to Algiers, repeated to Naples for Kirk with reference to his 374, July 10,
                    11 a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
